                                                               Basic Commands in Linux

1) Commands are actually files containing programs, often written in C. How will you find out in which directory does  the file corresponding to the man command resides?
   Answer : which command followed by argument is used to display the path of the argument 
            To display the path of the man command 
   Command: which man

2)How will you find out what is the use of the ps command.
   Answer : the ps command is to list the currently running processes and their PIDs and other information
            The commands used to know the use of ps command is :
	Command : whatis ps 
							(or)  
						ps --help
